When using the Creole TOC macro, these kind of comments turn up as level 1 entries in the TOC (which makes the TOC nearly useless since I am having a lot of code with comments):

{code}
#!python

# some comment
{code}

Hi !

I wanted to suggest a change in the emails, they are (sorry if it sounds agressive) unreadable.

Could you add items like:

* on which project the issue was written (I have a lot of repos, and I don&#x27;t always click on the link immidiatly if an issue is written)
* add a little description, the mail is too concrete: for example instad of

{code}
#!markdown

<USER>:
<issue details>
{code}

something like:

{code}
#!markdown

<USER> has written:
<issue details>
{code}

and so on.

* another idea would be to add styled emails. I&#x27;m a developper, so I know what blank text is, but my coworkers are community managers, they don&#x27;t :-)

Thanks !
